Vice President Kamala Harris will be visiting Nassau, The Bahamas on June 8 to meet with Caribbean leaders. The U.S.-Caribbean Leaders Meeting will be co-hosted by Vice President Harris and Prime Minister Philip Davis of The Bahamas. The meeting aims to strengthen cooperation between the United States and the Caribbean in areas such as prosperity, security, and climate resilience. This visit is part of the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to advancing relations with the Caribbean. The discussions will cover various regional issues, with a particular focus on addressing the climate crisis and promoting clean energy. The Vice President's trip also coincides with Caribbean-American Heritage Month, allowing for the celebration of the longstanding ties between the Caribbean and the United States.